# ============================================
# ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES - EXAMPLE/TEMPLATE
# ============================================
# 
# This file documents required environment variables for the Weather App.
# Copy this file to create your actual .env file:
# 
#   $ cp .env.example .env
# 
# Then replace placeholder values with your actual API keys.
#
# SECURITY WARNING:
# - .env.example: Safe to commit (no real secrets)
# - .env: NEVER commit to git (contains real API keys)
# 
# The .gitignore file excludes .env from version control.

# ============================================
# WEATHER API CREDENTIALS
# ============================================

# RapidAPI Key for Weather API
# SERVICE: RapidAPI (https://rapidapi.com)
# USED FOR: Fetching weather data for cities
# 
# HOW TO OBTAIN:
# 1. Create account at: https://rapidapi.com/
# 2. Subscribe to Weather API: https://rapidapi.com/weatherapi/api/weatherapi-com
# 3. Go to API dashboard
# 4. Copy "X-RapidAPI-Key" from code snippets
# 5. Paste value here (replace placeholder)
#
# EXAMPLE FORMAT:
# VITE_API_KEY=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
# CURRENT STATUS:
# ✗ This is a PLACEHOLDER - replace with your actual RapidAPI key
# ✓ The actual key should be ~50 characters alphanumeric
VITE_API_KEY=your_rapidapi_key_here